1
00:00:00,190 --> 00:00:01,960
I'm afraid my dad might not be okay with it.

2
00:00:02,370 --> 00:00:06,280
You know how fearsome and strict he is.

3
00:00:06,360 --> 00:00:07,320
Men being together?

4
00:00:07,370 --> 00:00:08,320
Are you crazy?

5
00:00:08,380 --> 00:00:09,160
Believe me!

6
00:00:09,210 --> 00:00:11,000
- Break up with him!
- Do I have to?

7
00:00:11,020 --> 00:00:12,340
I don't want to break up with you.

8
00:00:12,470 --> 00:00:14,240
I'll hold your hands
and go through this with you.

9
00:00:14,260 --> 00:00:15,900
I know you're disappointed.

10
00:00:15,950 --> 00:00:18,100
So am I.

11
00:00:18,460 --> 00:00:21,340
But he's not wrong
for making his own choices, either.

12
00:00:21,420 --> 00:00:24,260
Let him make his own decisions, alright?

13
00:00:25,160 --> 00:00:26,610
I'm sorry, honey.

14
00:00:27,220 --> 00:00:29,660
for not listening to you.

15
00:00:31,290 --> 00:00:33,480
- I'm so happy.
- Thank you for understanding me.

16
00:00:35,900 --> 00:00:37,140
You're my son;

17
00:00:37,480 --> 00:00:39,240
of course, I understand you.

18
00:00:39,760 --> 00:00:40,710
Grandpa!

19
00:00:41,030 --> 00:00:41,880
Grandpa!

20
00:01:07,360 --> 00:01:08,360
Grandpa!

21
00:01:08,560 --> 00:01:09,560
Grandpa!

22
00:01:09,760 --> 00:01:10,760
Grandpa.

23
00:01:16,080 --> 00:01:16,920
Hello.

24
00:01:16,960 --> 00:01:18,200
Someone is unconscious.

25
00:01:18,240 --> 00:01:19,280
Yes, the address is 11/11.

26
00:01:19,560 --> 00:01:20,200
Please hurry up.

27
00:01:20,240 --> 00:01:20,800
- Grandpa!
- Yes.

28
00:01:22,320 --> 00:01:23,200
- Grandpa.
- Grandpa!

29
00:01:23,360 --> 00:01:24,520
- Please hurry up.
- What happened?

30
00:01:24,560 --> 00:01:25,870
Grandpa.

31
00:01:25,910 --> 00:01:27,180
I just called an ambulance.

32
00:01:27,960 --> 00:01:29,760
[Disclaimer: All depicted events are fictional
and for entertainment purposes only

33
00:01:29,800 --> 00:01:30,680
Viewer discretion is advised]

34
00:03:09,600 --> 00:03:11,320
Mom, how's Grandpa?

35
00:03:11,360 --> 00:03:12,760
He's still in there.

36
00:03:19,880 --> 00:03:22,079
I'm sure he will be okay.

37
00:03:34,000 --> 00:03:36,020
How's Dad?

38
00:03:36,360 --> 00:03:38,240
We're still waiting. He's in there.

39
00:03:44,120 --> 00:03:45,120
- And...
- Here she is.

40
00:03:48,200 --> 00:03:50,480
- Is there a family member of Mr. Kan Nirun here?
- Yes, that's me.

41
00:03:50,520 --> 00:03:51,720
I'm his son.

42
00:03:51,760 --> 00:03:53,160
How is he?

43
00:03:54,120 --> 00:03:55,960
The patient's safe and stable,

44
00:03:56,120 --> 00:03:58,200
but the doctor has decided
to admit him for monitoring.

45
00:03:58,240 --> 00:03:59,710
- Okay.
- Anyway, please come this way.

46
00:03:59,750 --> 00:04:00,630
Yes, okay.

47
00:04:09,680 --> 00:04:11,000
Just a few more days,

48
00:04:11,040 --> 00:04:13,240
and if everything's alright,
he can go home.

49
00:04:13,480 --> 00:04:17,079
Please avoid letting him stay in the sun
for too long.

50
00:04:17,519 --> 00:04:19,170
Thank you so much, doctor.

51
00:04:19,800 --> 00:04:20,720
Thank you.

52
00:04:20,760 --> 00:04:21,600
Goodbye.

53
00:04:25,460 --> 00:04:27,460
I'll go get some food.

54
00:04:27,880 --> 00:04:29,280
Do you have anything in mind?

55
00:04:54,680 --> 00:04:56,190
We're getting some food.

56
00:04:56,230 --> 00:04:57,230
Wanna come with us?

57
00:05:02,960 --> 00:05:04,520
We'll catch up with you later.

58
00:05:27,520 --> 00:05:29,200
Are you still in shock?

59
00:05:37,560 --> 00:05:38,840
It's okay.

60
00:06:15,400 --> 00:06:16,780
Muenfah,

61
00:06:17,800 --> 00:06:19,600
thanks a lot for today.

62
00:06:20,120 --> 00:06:23,880
Without him, I have no idea
what would've happened to Grandpa.

63
00:06:25,520 --> 00:06:29,080
Actually, your son takes after you in this way,

64
00:06:30,600 --> 00:06:32,800
never showing weakness to anyone

65
00:06:34,159 --> 00:06:35,560
except the one he loves,

66
00:06:39,000 --> 00:06:42,800
and showing strength to the world

67
00:06:43,480 --> 00:06:45,070
not to worry anyone.

68
00:07:02,200 --> 00:07:03,160
Why...

69
00:07:07,120 --> 00:07:09,960
don't you take him to Grandpa?

70
00:07:21,120 --> 00:07:22,310
Can I?

71
00:07:26,800 --> 00:07:28,000
You're more than welcome to.

72
00:07:32,600 --> 00:07:33,670
Thank you.

73
00:07:37,920 --> 00:07:39,920
There's no need to stay at the hospital.

74
00:07:40,480 --> 00:07:42,560
It's normal for someone this old to fall.

75
00:07:43,880 --> 00:07:46,280
You need to stay here for now,

76
00:07:46,320 --> 00:07:49,120
and when you're back,
I won't let you water the plants anymore.

77
00:07:49,560 --> 00:07:51,560
That'll leave me with nothing to do,
feeling awfully lonely.

78
00:07:54,520 --> 00:07:56,680
I'll stay with you tonight.

79
00:07:56,840 --> 00:07:58,640
You should be with your mom.

80
00:07:59,120 --> 00:08:00,480
What about Mookrob?

81
00:08:00,760 --> 00:08:02,760
I bet our house is a mess now,

82
00:08:03,760 --> 00:08:05,760
I'll stay with you, then.

83
00:08:05,800 --> 00:08:07,360
Right, that's great.

84
00:08:07,400 --> 00:08:08,630
I'll be with you, too.

85
00:08:09,600 --> 00:08:10,680
You've got work to do.

86
00:08:10,720 --> 00:08:11,920
- What?
- Go finish it.

87
00:08:11,960 --> 00:08:12,960
You can come by tomorrow.

88
00:08:16,520 --> 00:08:17,660
Then...

89
00:08:18,000 --> 00:08:21,000
can I stay with you and Teerak?

90
00:08:23,600 --> 00:08:25,520
Right, that's nice.

91
00:08:25,840 --> 00:08:27,160
So there's someone with Rak here.

92
00:08:27,200 --> 00:08:28,960
Hold on, how can he stay?

93
00:08:29,000 --> 00:08:31,070
He didn't bring any clothes for tonight.

94
00:08:31,110 --> 00:08:32,919
For Teerak's clothes and stuff,

95
00:08:32,960 --> 00:08:34,960
I can ask Dom to go get them.

96
00:08:35,100 --> 00:08:36,390
- Right?
- Uh...

97
00:08:36,559 --> 00:08:37,520
Yes.

98
00:08:37,760 --> 00:08:39,280
I'll go get yours, too.

99
00:08:39,400 --> 00:08:40,840
Make sure you let your family know.

100
00:08:40,880 --> 00:08:42,400
Okay, thanks.

101
00:08:42,760 --> 00:08:44,640
That's settled, then.

102
00:08:44,680 --> 00:08:46,440
If I had gone home,

103
00:08:46,480 --> 00:08:48,800
all of this could've been avoided.

104
00:08:49,040 --> 00:08:50,800
You should stay here near the doctor.

105
00:08:51,200 --> 00:08:52,480
I'll be with you, too.

106
00:08:53,520 --> 00:08:54,760
No one thinks it's a big deal.

107
00:08:54,800 --> 00:08:56,070
And you won't feel lonely.

108
00:09:02,200 --> 00:09:03,300
Thanks.

109
00:09:14,280 --> 00:09:16,830
I was in shock, so I forgot to tell you this.

110
00:09:18,720 --> 00:09:20,000
Thank you, Fah.

111
00:09:20,920 --> 00:09:22,320
Without you,

112
00:09:22,880 --> 00:09:24,560
I wouldn't be able to get myself together.

113
00:09:30,240 --> 00:09:31,930
He's always been healthy.

114
00:09:32,880 --> 00:09:36,240
Every day, he would be watering the plants,

115
00:09:36,920 --> 00:09:38,920
taking Mookrob for a walk,

116
00:09:39,400 --> 00:09:42,320
or...playing chess all alone in the yard.

117
00:09:43,480 --> 00:09:44,680
However,

118
00:09:46,040 --> 00:09:48,080
taking our family for granted is frightening

119
00:09:49,770 --> 00:09:51,170
since we often don't realize...

120
00:09:51,760 --> 00:09:53,960
how much we neglect them.

121
00:09:58,360 --> 00:10:00,480
Watching him live his life alone

122
00:10:01,720 --> 00:10:04,880
and hearing him
play with Mookrob every morning became so normal.

123
00:10:06,110 --> 00:10:07,300
But today,

124
00:10:08,560 --> 00:10:10,160
I had no idea.

125
00:10:11,120 --> 00:10:12,800
I didn't hear him.

126
00:10:14,120 --> 00:10:15,720
If you weren't there...

127
00:10:20,000 --> 00:10:21,600
It's not your fault, Teerak.

128
00:10:23,480 --> 00:10:25,140
It's not anyone's fault.

129
00:10:26,680 --> 00:10:27,920
I believe...

130
00:10:28,440 --> 00:10:30,040
no one wanted this to happen.

131
00:10:32,680 --> 00:10:33,840
How about this?

132
00:10:34,240 --> 00:10:36,240
If you and your family let me,

133
00:10:37,040 --> 00:10:39,040
I'll play chess with Grandpa,

134
00:10:39,680 --> 00:10:41,080
so he won't be lonely.

135
00:10:42,520 --> 00:10:44,000
Thank you.

136
00:10:45,880 --> 00:10:47,610
Your family is my family, too.

137
00:10:50,120 --> 00:10:51,040
Come here.

138
00:11:18,560 --> 00:11:20,960
Who's watching who here?

139
00:11:23,400 --> 00:11:24,120
Uh...

140
00:11:24,480 --> 00:11:26,240
I think he'll be up soon.

141
00:11:26,600 --> 00:11:28,120
Do you want to eat anything else?

142
00:11:28,640 --> 00:11:30,240
I'll go grab some food for Teerak.

143
00:11:31,320 --> 00:11:32,600
He'll be hungry when he wakes up.

144
00:11:33,320 --> 00:11:35,560
Oh, this is enough for me.

145
00:11:35,600 --> 00:11:36,170
Okay.

146
00:11:36,840 --> 00:11:38,240
I'll be right back.

147
00:11:48,560 --> 00:11:50,080
Hey, Muenfah?

148
00:11:50,800 --> 00:11:51,960
Oh, hello.

149
00:11:56,800 --> 00:11:57,580
Oh...

150
00:11:58,360 --> 00:11:59,520
You bought them, too?

151
00:12:00,480 --> 00:12:01,200
Yes.

152
00:12:01,360 --> 00:12:02,760
I'm afraid Teerak will be hungry when he's up.

153
00:12:04,680 --> 00:12:06,880
These are also for him.

154
00:12:08,240 --> 00:12:10,730
Thanks a lot for taking care of him

155
00:12:11,120 --> 00:12:12,760
and my family.

156
00:12:13,200 --> 00:12:14,800
It's my pleasure.

157
00:12:18,720 --> 00:12:19,680
Fah!

158
00:12:23,640 --> 00:12:24,600
Hi, Dad.

159
00:12:28,440 --> 00:12:30,040
- This looks so good.
- How are you doing?

160
00:12:30,280 --> 00:12:32,360
I'm all good. I wanna go home.

161
00:12:32,520 --> 00:12:33,520
You'll get to go soon.

162
00:12:33,720 --> 00:12:34,980
You're healthy and strong.

163
00:12:35,520 --> 00:12:36,520
Hey, Rak.

164
00:12:37,360 --> 00:12:40,200
If he's allowed to go home tomorrow,

165
00:12:40,320 --> 00:12:42,040
Mom'll cook a big meal to celebrate that.

166
00:12:42,560 --> 00:12:43,640
- Really?
- Yes.

167
00:12:43,680 --> 00:12:44,640
That's nice.

168
00:12:46,720 --> 00:12:47,600
Muenfah,

169
00:12:50,440 --> 00:12:53,240
if you're free tomorrow, join us.

170
00:12:54,910 --> 00:12:55,720
Okay.

171
00:12:56,960 --> 00:12:57,960
I'm free.

172
00:13:10,720 --> 00:13:12,420
Here. That's good.

173
00:13:16,080 --> 00:13:19,040
Eat up, Grandpa, so you'll get stronger.

174
00:13:19,200 --> 00:13:21,640
I've never felt stronger.

175
00:13:23,440 --> 00:13:25,490
And where's Dom?

176
00:13:25,530 --> 00:13:26,640
He's not joining us?

177
00:13:26,680 --> 00:13:28,480
He has to be with his family today,

178
00:13:28,520 --> 00:13:29,840
- so he couldn't come.
- I see.

179
00:13:31,000 --> 00:13:32,870
Muenfah, eat up.

180
00:13:33,280 --> 00:13:35,680
I even asked her to do her best.

181
00:13:36,240 --> 00:13:38,540
It's to thank you for saving me.

182
00:13:38,720 --> 00:13:40,120
You're welcome.

183
00:13:40,280 --> 00:13:41,320
Right,

184
00:13:41,640 --> 00:13:42,900
when you have time,

185
00:13:42,940 --> 00:13:45,030
help me plant some trees in the yard.

186
00:13:45,920 --> 00:13:47,390
It's my yard.

187
00:13:47,880 --> 00:13:49,360
I don't care if the others won't let you,

188
00:13:49,400 --> 00:13:50,600
but I do.

189
00:13:57,280 --> 00:13:59,020
Have some protein, too.

190
00:14:00,160 --> 00:14:01,000
Here.

191
00:14:01,400 --> 00:14:02,880
Give some to Muenfah if that's too much.

192
00:14:06,320 --> 00:14:08,080
Give it to him yourself, then.

193
00:14:16,080 --> 00:14:17,840
You're right.

194
00:14:18,850 --> 00:14:20,630
- Here you go.
- Thank you.

195
00:14:24,880 --> 00:14:26,000
Eat up.

196
00:14:26,040 --> 00:14:27,620
Have some more if it's not enough.

197
00:14:29,080 --> 00:14:30,370
Right, Muenfah.

198
00:14:33,320 --> 00:14:36,180
After this meal, I want to talk to you.

199
00:14:37,400 --> 00:14:38,400
Okay.

200
00:14:53,240 --> 00:14:55,840
We may not have had...

201
00:14:56,160 --> 00:14:58,360
many conversations before.

202
00:14:59,560 --> 00:15:03,440
First of all, thank you

203
00:15:03,800 --> 00:15:05,200
for saving Grandpa.

204
00:15:05,640 --> 00:15:06,770
You're welcome.

205
00:15:07,440 --> 00:15:08,640
I'm willing to.

206
00:15:13,480 --> 00:15:15,560
There's one more thing that's...

207
00:15:17,080 --> 00:15:18,290
very important.

208
00:15:19,160 --> 00:15:27,120
I've hurt you with my actions and words,

209
00:15:30,400 --> 00:15:31,580
and I...

210
00:15:33,320 --> 00:15:40,120
really hope you'll be able to forgive me.

211
00:15:42,760 --> 00:15:44,400
I can't forgive you

212
00:15:46,720 --> 00:15:49,320
since I was never mad at you.

213
00:15:49,880 --> 00:15:53,200
I know you've done all of that

214
00:15:53,600 --> 00:15:55,400
just because you love Teerak.

215
00:16:00,600 --> 00:16:01,790
Thanks a lot.

216
00:16:07,880 --> 00:16:08,720
Well...

217
00:16:09,640 --> 00:16:12,520
In the past,

218
00:16:13,000 --> 00:16:17,400
the only thing I cared about
was for him to be happy,

219
00:16:17,920 --> 00:16:19,280
be in a complete family,

220
00:16:19,440 --> 00:16:22,240
and find someone
who can love him as much as I do.

221
00:16:25,640 --> 00:16:27,040
But I was wrong.

222
00:16:29,720 --> 00:16:32,680
I can see it now.

223
00:16:33,720 --> 00:16:35,790
Each person sees love differently.

224
00:16:37,040 --> 00:16:40,040
You can care for Teerak,

225
00:16:41,240 --> 00:16:43,840
and you've become his source of happiness.

226
00:16:45,440 --> 00:16:47,640
Teerak's grandpa once asked me

227
00:16:49,000 --> 00:16:50,200
what I wanted

228
00:16:50,400 --> 00:16:51,790
and what my intention was.

229
00:16:54,880 --> 00:16:56,680
Many answers just kept coming to my mind.

230
00:16:59,680 --> 00:17:02,760
But I've found the right answer today.

231
00:17:02,800 --> 00:17:05,200
It's simple, and it's the only one.

232
00:17:11,560 --> 00:17:15,560
I want Teerak to be happy.

233
00:17:16,359 --> 00:17:17,359
That's all.

234
00:17:22,720 --> 00:17:23,900
Muenfah,

235
00:17:25,800 --> 00:17:32,380
please make him feel happy.

236
00:17:37,680 --> 00:17:39,160
I promise

237
00:17:39,640 --> 00:17:42,920
to make him the happiest person.

238
00:17:54,000 --> 00:17:55,440
Don't you guys worry.

239
00:17:55,760 --> 00:17:58,320
Everything's gonna be okay. Trust me.

240
00:18:03,000 --> 00:18:04,400
They're here!

241
00:18:10,760 --> 00:18:11,480
Uh...

242
00:18:11,800 --> 00:18:13,120
What did you guys talk about?

243
00:18:14,280 --> 00:18:15,960
Nothing much.

244
00:18:16,320 --> 00:18:17,870
I just told him

245
00:18:17,910 --> 00:18:21,720
he's welcome to come over anytime,
as often as he likes.

246
00:18:24,600 --> 00:18:26,690
So that means...

247
00:18:27,120 --> 00:18:30,480
you're okay if we date?

248
00:18:32,280 --> 00:18:33,240
Yes.

249
00:18:39,110 --> 00:18:39,920
Yay!

250
00:18:39,960 --> 00:18:42,360
- Thanks, Dad.
- Alright.

251
00:18:45,600 --> 00:18:46,990
Care for each other, okay?

252
00:18:58,360 --> 00:18:59,270
Fah,

253
00:18:59,720 --> 00:19:01,720
what did you guys talk about?

254
00:19:01,760 --> 00:19:02,760
I wanna know.

255
00:19:03,600 --> 00:19:05,400
Your dad told me

256
00:19:06,120 --> 00:19:07,710
he wanted nothing from me

257
00:19:08,800 --> 00:19:11,200
but to see you be the happiest person.

258
00:19:16,920 --> 00:19:18,480
I've never questioned

259
00:19:19,120 --> 00:19:20,520
why your name means "the loved one."

260
00:19:21,400 --> 00:19:25,600
It's because you're adored
by everyone in your family.

261
00:19:29,760 --> 00:19:32,160
I'm really happy, you know that?

262
00:19:33,200 --> 00:19:35,000
So am I.

263
00:19:38,000 --> 00:19:39,230
I'm thankful

264
00:19:42,160 --> 00:19:43,760
you came into this world for me to love you.

265
00:19:48,560 --> 00:19:50,140
Thank you, too,

266
00:19:50,680 --> 00:19:52,280
for being with me through all of this.

267
00:19:55,880 --> 00:19:56,880
Fah,

268
00:20:02,240 --> 00:20:03,430
kiss me on the head.

269
00:20:05,120 --> 00:20:06,120
Please.

270
00:20:06,560 --> 00:20:08,320
Kiss me on the head.

271
00:20:08,680 --> 00:20:10,050
Please.

272
00:20:10,090 --> 00:20:12,490
Can you kiss me on the head?

273
00:20:12,880 --> 00:20:14,420
Fah,

274
00:20:16,520 --> 00:20:17,680
come on.

275
00:20:17,920 --> 00:20:19,250
Please.

276
00:20:20,600 --> 00:20:21,400
Okay.

277
00:20:43,040 --> 00:20:44,160
I did.

278
00:20:46,200 --> 00:20:48,160
Yay, you kissed me on the head!

279
00:21:19,360 --> 00:21:20,440
What is it, dear?

280
00:21:20,480 --> 00:21:22,600
What do you want, kiddo?

281
00:21:23,120 --> 00:21:26,930
Fah's told me what you said to him.

282
00:21:28,840 --> 00:21:29,720
So?

283
